        <h2>Football-Specific Planning Considerations</h2>
        <p>Football teams are typically the largest in the school — often 60-100 athletes plus coaches, families, and booster club members. Venue capacity is a critical first consideration.</p>

        <h3>Budget Tips for Football Banquets</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Average cost:</strong> $15-30 per person for a large football program</li>
          <li><strong>Start fundraising early:</strong> Concession stands at games can fund the entire banquet</li>
          <li><strong>Consider booster club sponsorships</strong> — local businesses often step up for football programs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Football Decoration Themes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Friday Night Lights</strong> — Stadium-themed with goal posts, yard markers, and stadium lighting</li>
          <li><strong>Gridiron Glory</strong> — Highlight season records and big wins with timeline displays</li>
          <li><strong>Helmet Display Tables</strong> — Mini helmets as part of each table centerpiece</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="product-note">
          <p><strong>🏈 Football Centerpieces:</strong> Custom 3D printed football centerpieces available in 8.75", 11.5", and 12" sizes. Each football features detailed laces and seam lines, available in your team's colors with optional personalization (player name, number, team name). These make excellent banquet table toppers and senior keepsakes.</p>
          <a href="https://lakeshore-gift.myshopify.com/products/football-graduation-centerpiece-8-3-4-football" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank">View Football Centerpieces →</a>
        </div>

        <h2>Football Banquet Award Categories</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Team MVP</strong> — The player who made the biggest impact</li>
          <li><strong>Offensive MVP</strong> — QB, RB, WR, or OL standouts</li>
          <li><strong>Defensive MVP</strong> — Linemen, linebackers, or DBs who dominated</li>
          <li><strong>Special Teams Player of the Year</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Most Improved Player</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Iron Horse Award</strong> — Most dedicated in the weight room</li>
          <li><strong>Scout Team Player of the Year</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Senior Night for Football</h2>
        <p>Football senior night is usually the last home game. Plan a ceremony that includes senior introductions with parents, a senior highlight video, and presentation of a commemorative item. Many programs give seniors a custom football centerpiece as a lasting memento of their career.</p>

        <p><a href="/senior-night/" class="btn btn-outline">Full Senior Night Guide →</a> <a href="/award-ceremony/" class="btn btn-outline">Award Ceremony Tips →</a></p>
